==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ædˈv̥ɛntʃɚ/ (CA)}}

*{{IPA| [[RP]] /ədˈvɛntʃə/}}

*{{Audio|en-ca-adventure.ogg|Audio (CA)}}

===Etymology 1===
From Old English ''[[aventure]]'', ''[[aunter]], ''[[anter]]'', from French ''[[aventure]]'', from late Latin ''[[adventurus]]'', from Latin ''[[advenire]]'', ''[[adventum]],'' "to arrive", which in the Romance languages took the  sense of "to happen, befall" (see also [[advene]])

====Noun====
{{en-noun-reg}}
# That which happens without [[design]]; [[chance]]; [[hazard]]; [[hap]]; hence, chance of danger or loss.
# The [[encounter]]ing of [[risk]]s; [[hazardous]] and [[striking]] [[enterprise]]; a [[bold]] [[undertaking]], in which hazards are to be encountered, and the issue is [[stake]]d upon [[unforeseen]] events; a [[daring]] feat.
# A [[remarkable]] [[occurrence]]; a striking event; a [[stir]]ring [[incident]]; as, the adventures of one's life.
# A [[mercantile]] or [[speculative]] enterprise of hazard; a [[venture]]; a [[shipment]] by a [[merchant]] on his own [[account]].

=====Antonyms=====
*(''remarkable occurence''): [[boredom]]

